08/06/2008
PRISTINA, Kosovo -- An international court in Pristina on Friday (June 6th) sentenced an ethnic Albanian to the maximum 40 years in prison for bombing a bus carrying Serb nationals in February 2001. The bombing killed 11 and injured 22, making it one of the deadliest terrorist acts in Kosovo since the end of the 1998-99 war. Florim Ejupi, 40, was convicted on 11 charges. (Blic, Reuters, AFP, AP, DPA - 06/06/08)
